Indestructible Design Premium 600D polyester is thick, sturdy and strong, yet flexible enough to fling over your shoulder. Repels water, wind, dirt and dust. Maximum Visibility Tote your gear late at night without worry. Reflective webbing is woven around the bag. Exceptional Organization With (8) distinct pockets and interior compartments (dividers included), it’s not a bag, but a complete storage system. Snag-Proof Zippers We replaced the usual buckles with high-quality reflective zipper closures—perfect for accessing your gear in a pinch.

Versatile Tool Loops Top flap loops in various sizes, so you can securely tote shears, tweezers, hemostats and more. Comfy Shoulder Strap A removable carry strap lightens your load with a padded section positioned over the shoulder. Great for neck and back pain. Name Card Slot Slip your name or business card into the window—then wear it proudly! Built to Last If your bag fails for any reason, Scherber is on call 24/7 to make it right.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well packaged Kit
reviews.reviewText: I used some leftover FSA funds to get this for our home. Well stocked and I'm confident it will serve us well in an emergency.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing, must have
reviews.reviewText: You should definitely get this if you have a family. It literally has everything you need for a medical emergency that is a simple knee scar to a possible neck injury.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quality Bag and Equipment, Love It
reviews.reviewText: Using this in my personal vehicle (I’m an EMT). I absolutely love the design and quality of the bag. The zippers zip and unzip with ease. This has a great variety of equipment to carry in your personal vehicle. Bag is the perfect size, just what I was looking for. Bag is not too bulky andnot too small either. I love the dividers and although I haven’t had a need to really move them a whole lot, I think it would be easy to adjust them. Started with this set and added a few things to it. Side pockets can hold quite a bit of stuff. Love the star of life logo on the top also. The black bag with the yellow reflective tape and the light blue/white star of life looks great. Overall, a great bag and great equipment. Great for first responders wanting to carry equipment in their personal vehicle. Love it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A great and very adaptable bag for first aid range needs
reviews.reviewText: Great product for the basic to advance user. Has everything and then some. Will be adding stuff to this jump bag of my preference, as would others. This fully stocked bag is a great resource for the basic user and very adaptable for more advance user. I feel confident now when working and running a range knowing I have this first aid kit with me!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 12, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality kit for intermediates
reviews.reviewText: Overall good quality- stocked with mainly Dynarex products. Note some of this gear (OPAs, bag valve mask, etc.) should only be used by a trained responder. Fortunately/unfortunately I have yet to use most the gear, but here’s my 2 cents from an EMR level of training.The good-Huge zippers, very smooth, easy accessQuality bagGood variety in products- airway, bleeding, burns, splinting, and other basicsGood to go as is for a general kitNice handles to grab and goGood sized size pockets with easy accessGenerally good quality supplies that work.The bad/my takesCould use some higher quantities of combine padsElastic loops are a little loose and some things fall out.Tourniquet is a little on the cheap side but might work in a pinchOnly comes with two pairs of glovesOverall a good kit for someone with some training- it rides in my vehicle daily

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great bag, has everything I need. Didn’t arrive with neck brace, contacted company through Amazon help. They immediately sent another neck brace and showed up fast. Very thankful for customer service support.
